{"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Group\/tint(_:)-22aak"},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI","doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Group"]]},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Sets the tint within this view."}],"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"],"tokens":[{"text":"nonisolated","kind":"attribute"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"tint","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"text":"S","kind":"genericParameter"},{"text":">(","kind":"text"},{"text":"_","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"tint","kind":"internalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"S","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":"?) -> ","kind":"text"},{"text":"some","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"View","preciseIdentifier":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore4ViewP","kind":"typeIdentifier","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/View"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"where","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"S","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":" : ","kind":"text"},{"text":"ShapeStyle","preciseIdentifier":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore10ShapeStyleP","kind":"typeIdentifier","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/ShapeStyle"},{"text":"\n","kind":"text"}]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"parameters":[{"name":"tint","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The tint to apply.","type":"text"}]}]}],"kind":"parameters"},{"content":[{"text":"Discussion","type":"heading","anchor":"discussion","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Use this method to override the default accent color for this view with","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"a given styling. Unlike an app’s accent color, which can be","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"overridden by user preference, tint is always respected and should","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"be used as a way to provide additional meaning to the control.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Controls which are unable to style themselves using the given type of"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ShapeStyle"},{"type":"text","text":" will try to approximate the styling as best as they can"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"(i.e. controls which can not style themselves using a gradient will"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"attempt to use the color of the gradient’s first stop)."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This example shows a linear gauge tinted with a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"gradient from "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/ShapeStyle\/blue","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" to "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/ShapeStyle\/red","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["struct ControlTint: View {","    var body: some View {","        Gauge(value: 75, in: 0...100) {","            Text(\"Temperature\")","        }","        .gaugeStyle(.linearCapacity)","        .tint(Gradient(colors: [.blue, .orange, .red]))","    }","}"]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Some controls adapt to the tint color differently based on their style,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the current platform, and the surrounding context. For example, in"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"macOS, a button with the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"PrimitiveButtonStyle\/bordered"},{"type":"text","text":" style doesn’t"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"tint its background, but one with the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"PrimitiveButtonStyle\/borderedProminent"},{"type":"text","text":" style does. In macOS, neither"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"of these button styles tint their label, but they do in other platforms."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"kind":"content"}],"metadata":{"title":"tint(_:)","symbolKind":"method","extendedModule":"OpenSwiftUICore","roleHeading":"Instance Method","platforms":[{"name":"iOS","beta":false,"deprecated":false,"unavailable":false,"introducedAt":"13.0"},{"name":"macOS","beta":false,"deprecated":false,"unavailable":false,"introducedAt":"10.15"},{"name":"tvOS","beta":false,"deprecated":false,"unavailable":false,"introducedAt":"13.0"},{"name":"visionOS","beta":false,"deprecated":false,"unavailable":false,"introducedAt":"1.0"},{"name":"watchOS","beta":false,"deprecated":false,"unavailable":false,"introducedAt":"6.0"}],"modules":[{"name":"OpenSwiftUI","relatedModules":["OpenSwiftUICore"]}],"fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"tint","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"text":"S","kind":"genericParameter"},{"text":">(","kind":"text"},{"text":"S","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":"?) -> ","kind":"text"},{"text":"some","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore4ViewP","text":"View","kind":"typeIdentifier"}],"externalID":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore4ViewPAAE4tintyQrqd__SgAA10ShapeStyleRd__lF::SYNTHESIZED::s:15OpenSwiftUICore5GroupV","role":"symbol","remoteSource":{"url":"https:\/\/github.com\/OpenSwiftUIProject\/OpenSwiftUI\/blob\/main\/Sources\/OpenSwiftUICore\/Shape\/Tint.swift#L47","fileName":"Tint.swift"}},"kind":"symbol","schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/openswiftui\/group\/tint(_:)-22aak"]}],"sections":[],"references":{"doc://OpenSwiftUI/documentation/OpenSwiftUI":{"kind":"symbol","role":"collection","url":"\/documen